pageContext.description: Bar circular in section, broken into 2 pieces. Thick in the middle, it narrows towards the ends. Probably this was the handle of a fibula, for the broken state of the ends show it to have been incomplete.
pageContext.collection: National Museum of Science and Art, Dublin,Plate XVI. 306 + Plate XVIII. 372. 103, 1881,Purchased with a number of other gold objects from Mrs. Perry.
